ZH: 他是一个虔敬的信徒，每周都会去教堂做礼拜。
EN: He is a devout believer who goes to church for worship every week.

ZH: 她虔敬地磕了三个头，给了长辈拜年。
EN: She respectfully kowtowed three times and wished the elders a Happy New Year.

ZH: 作为一名虔敬的佛教徒，他每天早晨都会念经。
EN: As a devout Buddhist, he recites sutras every morning.

ZH: 在这个虔敬的地方，人们向神明献上鲜花和香火。
EN: In this sacred place, people offer flowers and incense to the deities.

ZH: 妈妈常常教导我要虔敬地对待长辈和帮助他们。
EN: Mom often teaches me to treat elders with respect and help them devoutly.

ZH: 他的祖父是一个虔敬的宗教领袖。
EN: His grandfather is a devout religious leader.

ZH: 她把生活中的每一天都过得充满虔敬和感恩之心。
EN: She lives each day with devotion and gratitude.

ZH: 这个村庄的人们都非常虔敬地参与宗教活动。
EN: The people in this village participate in religious activities with great devotion.

ZH: 他对于自己的宗教信仰非常虔敬，从不违背信条。
EN: He is very devout in his religious beliefs and never goes against the tenets.

ZH: 我们要以虔敬的心去对待自然环境，保护我们的地球。
EN: We should treat the natural environment with reverence and protect our planet.

ZH: 每当我去祖父的墓前，我都会虔敬地祈祷并给他烧纸钱。
EN: Whenever I visit my grandfather's grave, I pray devoutly and burn joss paper for him.

ZH: 学生们都虔敬地站起来向老师敬礼。
EN: The students all stand up respectfully and salute the teacher.

ZH: 他虔敬地跪在地上，向神像行礼。
EN: He devoutly kneels on the ground and pays homage to the deity.

ZH: 这本书记录了一位虔敬的修行者的心路历程。
EN: This book records the spiritual journey of a devout practitioner.

ZH: 在这个庙宇里，每天都有许多人来虔敬地祈祷。
EN: In this temple, many people come daily to pray devoutly.

ZH: 她虔敬地燃起蜡烛，为逝去的亲人祈祷。
EN: She devoutly lights a candle and prays for her departed loved ones.

ZH: 我们应该以虔敬的态度去学习和尊重传统文化。
EN: We should approach the study and respect for traditional culture with reverence.

ZH: 这位教授是一位虔敬的信徒，在学术领域有着崇高的声誉。
EN: The professor is a devout believer and has a great reputation in the academic field.

ZH: 在这个宗教节日里，信徒们会隆重、虔敬地庆祝。
EN: During this religious festival, the believers will celebrate with grandeur and reverence.

ZH: 他每天早上都会虔敬地向上帝祷告一段时间。
EN: He devoutly prays to God for some time every morning.
